Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Arrange @bacon{4%oz} 1-2 inches apart on a #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack until crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once bacon is crispy, transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Dice @Roma tomatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces.

== Cheesy Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Arborio rice{3/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until translucent, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in 3 cups water, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, two of the @chicken stock concentrate{4}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has evaporated and rice is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: If liquid evaporates before rice is tender, add a splash more water.

== Bacon Jam ==

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @red pepper jam{3}, scallion whites, chopped bacon, half the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, and 1 1/2 TBSP water. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{45%seconds}.

Uncover and stir bacon jam; chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

== Stew ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir in diced tomatoes, @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, @Cajun spice blend{1%tbsp}, and remaining paprika. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes soften, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in 2 cups water, remaining stock concentrates, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Once stew has slightly thickened, stir in shrimp. Return to a simmer and cook until shrimp are opaque and cooked through, ~{5%minutes} more.

== Cornbread Swirls ==

Open tube of @cornbread swirls{11%oz}; separate and place 1-2 inches apart on a second baking sheet. Bake on top rack until golden brown, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Finish Rice ==

Once rice is almost tender, stir in @cream sauce base{4%oz}. Return to a simmer and cook until rice is creamy and liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide cheesy rice and stewed shrimp between #bowls{} in separate sections. Dollop rice with as much bacon jam as you like. Garnish shrimp with scallion greens. Serve with cornbread swirls on the side.